A UNIQUE CAREER OPPORTUNITY

BRP is looking to recruit a new business intelligence analyst within the Data & Marketing insights team. In this position, you will contribute to the development and optimization of the data platform allowing the consolidation and standardization of data sources. You will develop a deep understanding of the marketing data technology ecosystem and will be responsible to maintain data integrity. You will also contribute to provide information and insights to our business partners.

Interested? We are looking for a bright individual who loves data and analytics and who demonstrates a willingness to go the extra mile, takes on the responsibility of doing what needs to be done, has a positive attitude and rolls with changes. This person will have a great opportunity to join a committed and talented team of data enthusiasts.

YOUR KEY RESPONSIBILITIES
Contribute and support the development of analytics and process optimization.
Work closely with the IS&T department on data integration and management.
Develop complex reports and dashboards and monitor data reporting issues and performance.
Ensure data integrity and consistency across marketing analytical tools.
YOUR QUALIFICATIONS AND SKILLS
University degree in computer science, information technology, business intelligence or another related field;
Minimum 3 years of relevant experience in business intelligence;
Strong knowledge of database engineering, ETL processes, and integration tools;
Experience with data preparation, and processing in a cloud environment, Azure a plus;
Passion for data and flexible, creative approach to problem solving;
Experience with a data visualization tool and a statistical programming language is a plus;
Excellent communication (both verbal and written).
Here are some key tools with which you should be familiar:
Azure;
SQL;
Power BI;
SAS;
Python.
