5 to 10 years of biological experience working in Alberta (British Columbia experience a plus);
Knowledge of environmental regulations including AER and AEP;
Knowledge of provincial & state protected species and permitting requirements;
Experience using GPS units in the field (prior use of ArcPad, GIS, Collector, Survey123 a plus);
Strong attention to detail and ability to multitask effectively;
Excellent analytical and judgement capabilities;
Field experience with ability to travel to job sites in remote locations;
Ability to work during evenings and/or weekends as needed;
Ability to travel to various job sites and spend most, if not all, of the work day on-site and meet with clients, as required;
Must have a valid driver’s license in good standing and reliable transportation to visit job sites as needed; and
Reside in Calgary or surrounding region.
